From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pantavisor <developer@pantavisor.io>
Subject: [PATCH] meson: do not force gold linker

The gold linker has been deprecated as of GNU binutils 2.44 (Feb 2025)
and will be removed unless new maintainers step forward. Google, its
original developer, has moved to the LLVM toolchain and LLD.

More critically, gold on aarch64 miscomputes __EH_FRAME_BEGIN__ in
crtbeginS.o, causing frame_dummy to pass address 0x0 to
__register_frame_info. This crashes in strlen() when libgcc_s parses
bogus CIE augmentation data during dlopen() of liblxc.so.

The __register_frame_info mechanism is obsolete for shared libraries
(replaced by .eh_frame_hdr + PT_GNU_EH_FRAME), but the constructor in
crtbeginS.o still fires, and the wrong address causes a SIGSEGV.

Remove the forced gold linker selection and use the distro default
linker (typically ld.bfd) instead.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Pantavisor <developer@pantavisor.io>
---
 meson.build | 5 -----
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/meson.build b/meson.build
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -230,11 +230,6 @@ possible_link_flags = [
     '-fstack-protector-strong',
 ]

-# The gold linker fails with a bus error on sparc64
-if build_machine.cpu_family() != 'sparc64'
-    possible_link_flags += '-Wl,-fuse-ld=gold'
-endif
-
 if sanitize == 'none'
     possible_link_flags += '-Wl,--warn-common'
 endif
